Articles.Content:
Is it possible to set a min and max limit on, say, a rototron and then tie to a joystick axis? I don't know anything about the difficulties involved with this but it would allow for custom flight surfaces . . . would be very useful. Possibly tie it in with Advanced Fly By Wire?

**Edited <time datetime="2016-02-05T17:16:12Z" title="02/05/2016 05:16  PM" data-short="8 yr">February 5, 2016</time> by Styles2304**

> 
> 
> On 2/5/2016 at 5:15 PM, Styles2304 said:
> 
> 
> Is it possible to set a min and max limit on, say, a rototron and then tie to a joystick axis? I don't know anything about the difficulties involved with this but it would allow for custom flight surfaces . . . would be very useful. Possibly tie it in with Advanced Fly By Wire?
> 

This is slightly beyond the scope of IR, but you can do it yourself using kOS - look for Mecanum wheels script in Zoduis's for inspiration

So I've tried the 0.21.4 from curse and from kerbalstuff but it always makes my game stop loading at:

![ubxsgLj.png](http://i.imgur.com/ubxsgLj.png)

Modulemanager is, like KSP/IR/Tweakscale, the newest available version.

Edit: Even without TweakScale and MM it refuses to start ...
